Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createPipelineBusGuide(25.10)                    createPipelineBusGuide(25.10)

Name
       createPipelineBusGuide - Generates bus-guide for the pipeline netgroup

Syntax
       createPipelineBusGuide

       [-help]

       [-netGroup <netGroupNames>]

       [-widthFactor <value>]

       [-layer <id1:id2>]

       [-report <fileName>]

       [-spacing <value> {-report <filename>}]

       Generates bus-guide for the pipeline netgroup. The bus-guide is used to
       guide the router for expected path. It can be used in the analysis flow
       or after the pipeline flops are inserted in the netlist.

       Note:  The  bus-guide  width  is  scalable by the width factor. Default
       width factor is 1.0. The bus width equals to the (width factor) x  (the
       largest  pitch  of given routing layers) x (the number of bus bits) + 1
       extra pitch. The extra pitch is added to account  for  the  possibility
       that bus-guides do not line up exactly with the routing grid.

Parameters
       -netGroup <netGroupNames>
              Specifies  the  netgroup  name(s)  that the bus-guide is created
              for.

              Default: ""

       -widthFactor <value>
              Specifies the width factor of bus-guide.

              Default: 1.0

       -layer <id1:id2>
              Specifies the layer(s) to use for the  generated  bus-guide.  It
              can be a single layer or layer range.

              Default: all

       -report <fileName>
              Specifies the analysis report file name.

              Default: <filename>.rpt

       -spacing <float>
              Specifies the maximum space between flops. Default: ""

Example
              * The  following command writes out a report file 'busguide.rpt'
                which tells the total estimated length of  bus  (in  microns),
                the  number  of stages that will be needed (based on the given
                spacing of 200 um), and location of each stage of PFFs for all
                net groups on all routing layers.

                createPipelineBusGuide -spacing 200 -report busguide.rpt

              * The following command create bus-guide for net group 'NG1'  on
                routing layers 2, 3, and 4. The bus-guide width is 2 times the
                default width.

                createPipelineBusGuide  -netGroup  NG1 -widthFactor 2.0 -layer
                2:4

